==Galician==
===Etymology===
Attested since circa 1300. From Old Galician and {{inh|gl|roa-opt|joya}} (independently attested in both corpora), from {{der|gl|fro|joie}}, from {{m|fro|joiel}} (modern {{m|fr|joyau}}), from {{der|gl|VL.|*jocale}}, from {{der|gl|la|iocus|jocus}}. {{doublet|gl|xoel}}.
Compare {{cog|pt|joia}} and {{cog|es|joya}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|gl|[ˈʃɔjɐ]}}
